      • FloatParameter

               java.lang.String fieldName,
               java.lang.String labelText,
               float initialValue,
               float minValue,
               float maxValue,
               float valueScaling)
        Creates a FloatParameter with a slider.
        Parameters:
        obj - the object that contains the field to be controlled.
        fieldName - the name of the field on the object that this should control. Should be of type float.
        labelText - the text displayed beside the control.
        initialValue - the initial value of the textbox.
        minValue - the lower bound of the slider.
        maxValue - the upper bound of the slider.
        valueScaling - a factor by which to scale the value before passing it on to the object.
